cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SE 

The paper deals with security issues in mobile ad hoc networks (MANETs), which are wireless networks without a fixed infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the communication and computation overhead of the proposed protocol, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents a key exchange protocol, which could be relevant to the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of designing a protocol for resource-constrained nodes, which could be relevant to the category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
